sations and partners</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="26" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">Mrs Bourne has been influential in renewing </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">and increasing </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">the</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt"> pace of</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt"> collaboration</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">with Surrey </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">Police setting out </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">how</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt"> both</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt"> forces will work together in the future. Th</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">e vision commits to a future of</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">‘Sussex </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">and Surrey </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">Police working as one, operationally and organisationally, to enhance and improve services for the public</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">whilst reducing cost</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">s and responding to local needs</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">’</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="27" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">It is important to emphasise that Sussex and Surrey each raise their precept funding separately in their </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">own </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">force area</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt"> and will continue to have a </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">Police &amp; Crime </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">Commissioner and </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">a </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">Chief Constable for each county.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="28" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">The Commissioner is </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">also </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">supportive of the creation of a South East Regional Organised Crime Unit and Counter Terrorism</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt"> Unit</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">, </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">which is hosted</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">by</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt"> Thames Valley</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt"> Police</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt"> in line with the Serious and Organised Crime Strategy.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="29" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">Mrs Bourne is an influential member of the Sussex Criminal Justice Board and would like to become chair to assist in the coordination of the criminal justice activity in Sussex.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="30" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">In addition, the Commissioner is also a</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt"> Director </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">of the College of Policing Board, a member of the HMIC Domestic Abuse &amp; Victims Reference Group and a member of the Ministry of Justice Transforming Rehabilitation</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt"> PCC</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt"> Reference Group. Mrs Bourne will become a member of the Police ICT Board when it is established.   </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">Transparency of and reporting by commissioners to date</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="31" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:10pt">The Commissioner is fully compliant with the code of recommended practice for local authorities on data transparency through</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-siz